cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with proof complexity of deep inference systems for propositional logic.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the simulation of Resolution and Frege systems, which are related to computational complexity.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are possible categories as the paper uses atomic flows, which are a type of diagram used in graph theory and combinatorics.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with automated reasoning and proof search.
